{"type":"message","id":"ab3eaa26","parentId":"e221cf97","timestamp":"2026-07-12T09:13:24.592Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ef64c41456254b83863fa97b","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-12-sovereign-access-risk.md","content":"# Sovereign Access Risk\n\n**Published:** 2026-07-12 09:13 UTC\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7481999117481766912/\n**Image:** boring-agents-1783699220.png\n**Characters:** 1127\n\n---\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗺𝗼𝗱𝗲𝗹 𝗱𝗶𝘀𝗮𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗮𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗿𝗻𝗶𝗴𝗵𝘁. 𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗦𝗟𝗔 𝗱𝗶𝗱𝗻'𝘁 𝗰𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗿 𝗶𝘁.\n\nThree weeks ago, the US government disabled Anthropic's Fable 5 for every foreign national. No warning. No exception. Just gone.\n\nEnterprise contracts didn't help. Force majeure clauses. Compliance catch-alls. Nothing about a government kill switch.\n\nThat event created a new risk category: sovereign access risk. When a government can flip off your AI model overnight, pricing and benchmarks become secondary.\n\nZ.ai just shipped the answer: GLM-5.2, MIT-licensed, trained entirely on Huawei chips, 82% cheaper than Claude Opus 4.8. Download it. Host it yourself. No export controls. No foreign kill switch.\n\nThe catch: if you use their cloud, Chinese law applies. The only way out is pure self-hosting.\n\nThis isn't about picking a model. It's about asking: Will this tool still work tomorrow? And who decides?\n\nYour vendor's SLA doesn't cover geopolitics.\n\n#AI #EnterpriseAI #Sovereignty #OpenSource #Geopolitics\n\n---\n\n## Performance\n\n_Stats will be added after 24-48 hours_\n\n- Views: _pending_\n- Likes: _pending_\n- Comments: _pending_\n- Shares: _pending_\n"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-12-sovereign-access-risk.md\", \"content\": \"# Sovereign Access Risk\\n\\n**Published:** 2026-07-12 09:13 UTC\\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7481999117481766912/\\n**Image:**